sentences: Christopher Niles Cox (born July 15) is an American dance music record producer, remixer, and DJ who has worked on over 600 records throughout his career.
Chris lives in Las Vegas with his dog Hammy.
Cox has produced original music and dance remixes for  Madonna, Rihanna, Michelle Branch, Hilary Duff, Donna Summer, Kelly Osbourne, and Kelly Clarkson.
For four years he was heard weekly on XM's BPM 81 with his hour-long set, "12 Inches of Cox."
In 2008 he produced the album Hannah Montana 2: Non-Stop Dance Party, which spent several weeks at #1 on the Billboard Dance/Electronic Albums Chart. .
